cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper deals with the problem of collaborative object transportation using multiple Micro Aerial Vehicles (MAVs). This falls under the domain of robotics and hence cs.RO is the most likely sub-category. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper employs techniques from robust control theory to choose the physical parameters of each agent to guarantee stability. This falls under the domain of systems and control and hence cs.SY is the second most likely sub-category. 
3. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper deals with multiple agents (MAVs) collaborating to transport an object. This falls under the domain of multi-agent systems and hence cs.MA is the third most likely sub-category. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper may involve some level of decision-making by the agents to achieve the task of object transportation. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence and hence cs.AI is the fourth most likely sub-category. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper does not explicitly mention the use of machine learning techniques, but it is possible that some form of learning may be employed by the agents to improve their performance. Hence, cs.LG is the fifth most likely sub-category.
